Start the Web Server: 							if ChromeBook (cloud9)   
	> python manage.py runserver  					(add behind cmd) 0.0.0.0:8080    
	In the Browser: 127.0.0.1:8000   

Start the virtual environment:
	> source blog/bin/activate 
End the ..:
	> deactivate

Update:
	> python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip   

Create a virtual environment:
	> python3 -m venv my_venv_name  
	(keep the venv name short cause we'll use it a lot)     

Get all the requirements: 
	> pip install -r requirements.txt  

Start a django project automatically:
	> django-admin startproject mysite .   

Create Database: 
	> python manage.py migrate  

Create an Application: 
	> python manage.py startapp blog_app   

Add the model (modified/ created) to the database: 
	let Django know we make some changes 
	> python manage.py makemigrations blog_app  
	> python manage.py migrate blog_app   
 
Create a superuser (admin): 
	> python manage.py createsuperuser   







   
